version_description: Chords here are sometimes quite technical to match the song as much as possible, however you can just simply Cadd4 to F if you wish.
The chords in this version sync and sound well with the music and vocals in the original song. They are fairly simple for a novice guitarist to play, and the chord changes are not too fast.
This is the perfect Original straight from my ear. You can play a Dm/D instead of a Dm/F if you prefer that sound.

version_description: The whole song and the rap is included in this version. This song is amazing, and it has a really great message behind it. Play it in the capo 3, or transpose (plus) 3 to play at the original key.

This is the last beautiful song by Sia, "The Greatest". Here there the chords, in the original key. If you want play it easier, put the capo on 3rd and play the chords three steps down. The G#maj7 can also be played with a simple G#. Hope you enjoy.
This is the right version, with capo on 3.
No capo needed. Chords from Sia's youtube music video of "The Greatest".
This is the full single with Lamar's rap. No capo needed.
All parts included (including instrumentals, intro, outro), corrected and timed chords, extra lyrics, strum pattern. Includes optional tab for playing style.
Some parts do not have obvious chords, so I found things that worked with the vocals. It's a wonderful song that will accompany a (hopefully) wonderful movie.
